id: pm-4ak1
title: "Repo-wide 100% docstring coverage: public API + data contracts (gate-enforced)"
description: "Raise TSDoc coverage to 100% across the exported/public-API and data-contract surface of src/ and packages/, and extend the static docstring gate so 100% is mandatory and cannot regress. Chosen tier: module docs + every exported declaration (incl consts) + every exported interface/type member + public class members, across src/ AND packages/. Baseline measured 2026-07-04: 2783/6740 (41.3%), 3957 missing across 188 files. Duplicate check: pm search 'docstring'/'code documentation' found only the closed pm-p4mw (src-only, top-level-exports-only gate) and closed coverage items; no open item covers packages, exported consts, or interface/type members — this epic extends that lineage."
type: Epic
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags[5]: coverage,docs,docstrings,quality,source
created_at: "2026-07-04T20:17:55.271Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-04T20:56:40.910Z"
assignee: maintainer-agent
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: "Static quality gate enforces 100% for: module docs (src+packages), exported declarations incl consts (src+packages), exported interface/type members, public class members; boilerplate+trivial-stub checks pass; gate spec at 100% coverage; pnpm build + typecheck + contracts green."
parent: pm-u9d0
risk: medium
confidence: high
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-04T20:56:40.910Z",codex-agent,"Audit note from all-status PM review 2026-07-04: this claimed epic is the only active item returned by pm list --status open,in_progress --filter-metadata-missing and --filter-estimates-missing. It already has parent/tags/AC/risk/confidence/assignee and 8 active children; missing fields are estimated_minutes plus reviewer/sprint/release. I did not take over the claim from maintainer-agent; please add the missing planning metadata during the docstring lane update."
body: "# Charter — Repo-wide public-API + data-contract docstring coverage\n\n## Goal\nRaise documentation coverage to 100% across the public API and data-contract\nsurface of `src/` and `packages/`, and make that level mandatory by extending\nthe existing static docstring gate so it can never regress.\n\n## Scope (chosen tier: \"Public API + data contracts\")\nMandatory TSDoc on:\n- every module (`@module` header) in `src/` and `packages/` (non-`.d.ts`, non-spec);\n- every exported top-level declaration, INCLUDING exported `const`/`let`/`var`\n  (the previous gate only required exported functions/classes/interfaces/types/enums);\n- every member of every exported `interface`;\n- every property member of every exported object-literal `type` alias;\n- every PUBLIC member (method/accessor/property + parameterized constructor) of\n  every exported `class`.\n\nOut of scope (documented only where non-obvious, NOT gate-enforced): non-exported\ninternal helpers/consts, private/protected/`#` class members, members of\nnon-exported interfaces/types/classes, enum members.\n\n## Baseline (measured 2026-07-04, TypeScript AST probe)\n- Enforced gate before this epic: 100% for src module docs + src top-level exports.\n- Chosen-tier coverage: 2783/6740 documented (41.3%); **3957 missing** across 188 files.\n- Dominant buckets: interface members 3566, exported consts 316, package module\n  docs 19, package exports ~53, exported type/interface/class headers ~15.\n\n## Quality bar (best practice / TSDoc + TypeDoc)\n- Describe WHAT the symbol represents and WHY it exists / how it is used across\n  the CLI/SDK/MCP/storage surfaces — never restate the identifier name.\n- State units, invariants, defaults, nullability, and side effects where relevant.\n- Cross-reference related symbols with `{@link}`; reference settings keys and\n  flags in backticks.\n- No boilerplate; the gate rejects template stubs and name-only docstrings.\n\n## Enforcement\n`scripts/release/static-quality-gate.mjs` extended to measure and require 100% of\nthe above across `src/` + `packages/`, plus a conservative trivial-stub check.\nRegression coverage added to `tests/unit/scripts/release/static-quality-gate.spec.ts`\n(the gate script is itself under the 100% coverage requirement).\n\n## Acceptance\n- Static quality gate reports the new coverage checks at 100% with zero missing\n  and zero boilerplate/trivial-stub violations.\n- `pnpm build`, typecheck, gate spec, and `pnpm contracts:*` remain green."
